        <detaileddescription>
<para>computes distance (height) map for given projection parameters using float-precision for finding ray-mesh intersections, which is faster but less reliable Generated from function <computeroutput>MR::Cuda::computeDistanceMap</computeroutput>. Parameter <computeroutput>mesh</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>params</computeroutput> can not be null. It is a single object. Parameter <computeroutput>cb</computeroutput> has a default argument: <computeroutput>{}</computeroutput>, pass <computeroutput>MR_PassBy_DefaultArgument</computeroutput> and a null pointer to use it. Parameter <computeroutput>outSamples</computeroutput> defaults to a null pointer in C++. Never returns null. Returns an instance allocated on the heap! Must call <computeroutput><ref refid="expected__MR__DistanceMap__std__string_8h_1a0a335b47ce20d18bf52ab4847d97e275" kindref="member">MR_expected_MR_DistanceMap_std_string_Destroy()</ref></computeroutput> to free it when you&apos;re done using it. </para>
